{
  "text": "Detecting a specific capsid antibody in serum suggests an HPV infection. Although more than 50% of infected subjects will have a serological conversion, and thus detection of HPV antibodies. This has been used to analyse the natural history and the cumulative infection in different groups [CITATION_1] . Assays measuring functional neutralising ability might reflect protective immunity, based on animal experiments. Nonetheless, epitopes for HPV are not completely characterised in human responses therefore, they will be heterogeneous [CITATION_2] . Herney Andr\u00e9s Garc\u00eda-Perdomo et al.",
